"""Bank of Canada (Valet) — rates, FX, and monetary data client.

Sandbox name: ``bank_of_canada_client``.

The Bank of Canada Valet web service publishes the Bank's financial and
monetary data: the policy (overnight target) rate, CORRA, Government of
Canada benchmark bond yields, daily/monthly FX rates, monetary
aggregates, the Bank of Canada commodity price index (BCPI), and more.
Two organising primitives:

  * series — a single time series, addressed by name (e.g. "FXUSDCAD",
    "V39079" the overnight rate target, "AVG.INTWO" = CORRA).
  * group  — a named bundle of related series (e.g. "FX_RATES_DAILY",
    "bond_yields_benchmark").

Progressive disclosure:

  L1  this module's signature + triggers (always-on).
  L2  the embedded ontology — every Valet series name->label and every
      group name->label (~15,600 series, ~2,400 groups). Search it offline
      to find the right series/group BEFORE any network call.
  L3  on-demand detail — get_series_detail(name) / get_group_detail(name)
      pull the live description + (for groups) member series.
  L4  data — get_observations(series, ...) / get_group_observations(group)
      return clean, date-keyed, coerced observations.

Base URL: https://www.bankofcanada.ca/valet  (anonymous, no auth).
Transport: Bucket A — session_and_auth() (standard requests + GS Kerberos
proxy adapter in PRISM; vanilla requests through the staging stub mirror).
"""

from __future__ import annotations

import json
import re
import unicodedata
from typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional, Sequence, Union

import requests

from ai_development.mcp.gs_app_proxy_negotiate import session_and_auth


VALET_BASE = "https://www.bankofcanada.ca/valet"
DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 60


class BankOfCanadaError(Exception):
    """Raised on a Valet request or validation failure."""


